sense.s:
He (a man) was long distant from his home; expl. by TaAlato 
								gurobatuhu; (K;) or was long in a state of celibacy; 
								TAlt Euzobatuhu, as in one copy of the K; (TA;) and became little in need, or little desirous, of women. (K.)

MvimapN, (S,) and MvimaAtN, (S, M, K, [in the CK, erroneously, AavimAtN.]) A she-camel, (S,) and she-camels, slow, or tardy; (S, M, K;) weary, fatigued, or jaded. (K. [In the CK, we find muEiyobAtN erroneously put for muEoyiyaAtN.]) Some pronounce it with t. (Sgh.) [In like manner,] 
							muWaAvimN↓ signifies That is slack, or slow, in pace, or going; 
								AalRaciI yakocibu fiI AlsRayori. (Sgh, K. [In Golius's Lex., as from the K, AalRaciI yukacRibu AlsRayora. Both are correct, signifying the same.])

10. AstOHd He (a man, S) was, or became, alone, by himself, apart from others, or solitary; 


							syn. Ainofarada; (S, K;) as also 
							QtRaHada↓ [written with the disjunctive alif AitRaHada, originally AiYotaHada or AiwtaHada], (K, TA,) or tawaHRada. (CK.)

5. tOmRr He became made, or appointed, commander, governor, lord, prince, or king; (Msb;) he received authority, power, or dominion; 
								Ealayohimo 
								over them. (S, K.) [See also Oamara.]
